All items below have been implemented.

# ROUND 1 — milestone 3 baseline (already done previously)

1. [DONE] Separate UIs for vendor and customer based on logins.
   - /login route, role + vendor selection persisted in zustand.
   - Role-aware header nav, cart hidden from vendors.
   - Route guards on /vendor, /cart, /quick-order, /vendors/$vendorId,
     /orders, /orders/:id, /manage. SSR-safe (typeof window guard).
2. [DONE] Mobile-first responsive design (hamburger menu, wrapping rows).
3. [DONE] Real-time vendor-driven progress (no auto-advance, cross-tab
   storage sync via useApp.persist.rehydrate()).
4. [DONE] 12-hour times (format12 / formatDate12) and queue-based pickup
   suggestion (suggestedPickupForVendor + min on input).
5. [DONE] Extra instructions textarea on cart, shown on order detail and
   vendor dashboard.
6. [DONE] Footer copy fixed.
7. [DONE] Sequential order numbers (1001+, persisted with migrate).


# ROUND 2 — secure login, manage page, statuses, animations

8. [DONE] Username + password login (no role tab).
   - Static "backend" users in src/data/users.ts. Login form is a single
     username + password field, secure-styled (lock + show/hide toggle,
     fake submit delay). On success, role is decided server-side and the
     user is bounced to /vendor or back to where they came from.
   - Demo creds shown on the form: customer `demo / demo123`, vendor
     `raju / raju123`.

9. [DONE] User profile chip in the header.
   - Default avatar (User / ChefHat icon) on dark background + truncated
     username, sitting immediately to the left of "Sign out".
   - Old time clock pill removed entirely from the header.
   - Sign-in CTA shown when not logged in.

10. [DONE] Manage page (/manage, vendor only).
    - Five fixed categories: Breakfast, Desi, Fastfood, Chinese, Drinks
      (replacing the old dinner/lunch/burgers grouping). Cards show a
      representative photo + item count.
    - Each card has Add Item (with picture upload via FileReader) and
      Edit Category (modal: edit names/prices/descriptions/images,
      delete items). Vendor edits persist to localStorage and propagate
      live to the customer view.
    - Customer view (/vendors/:id) gets the same category cards on top,
      tapping one smooth-scrolls to that section.

11. [DONE] Status overhaul: added a Cancelled status + color tokens.
    - New tokens in styles.css: --warning (yellow) and --success (green).
    - Single source of truth: src/lib/orderStatus.ts (statusPillClasses,
      statusDotClasses, statusLabel, STAGE_FLOW).
    - Color mapping:
        Pending     -> muted / blank
        Preparing   -> warning yellow
        Ready       -> success green
        Picked up   -> primary terracotta orange
        Cancelled   -> destructive red, labelled "Not accepted"
    - Applied on vendor dashboard pill, customer order detail badge,
      stage banners, and My Orders list.

12. [DONE] Cancel flow.
    - Vendor "Decline" sets the order to Cancelled (no longer "Picked up"
      as before).
    - Customer order detail shows a clear "Your order was not accepted"
      banner with no payment-charged note, and the cancelled card switches
      to a destructive border instead of the gradient.

13. [DONE] Vendor dashboard redesign.
    - Orders are now a 1 / 2 / 3-column GRID of prominent blocks (was
      cramped rows). Each block:
        - status pill (color-coded) docked top-right
        - order # huge, customer name + items below
        - pickup time + payment + notes block
        - action buttons docked at the bottom (Decline / Accept on
          Pending; Mark X on Preparing/Ready; locked label on closed
          orders) — sized so they're tap-friendly but not accidental.
    - Stat row is grid-cols-2 on phones (2x2) and grid-cols-4 on lg.
    - Added animated insertion/removal with framer-motion AnimatePresence.

14. [DONE] Quick order goes through full checkout.
    - "Tap to order" / "Reorder" now adds the items to the cart and
      navigates to /cart instead of placing instantly. The customer
      picks time, payment, and adds a note before confirming.

15. [DONE] Cart UX cleanup.
    - Replaced the bare clock <input> with a "Select time" / "Change
      time" button that programmatically opens the native time picker
      via showPicker(). No more clock icon as the only affordance.
    - Removed the queue-explanation paragraph; the suggestion is still
      enforced silently (input min + a soft snap-back if a too-early
      time is typed).

16. [DONE] My Orders calendar filter.
    - Date stepper + Popover Calendar (react-day-picker), defaults to
      Today. Days that have orders show a primary-colored dot. Toggle
      "Show all" to see the full history, "Today" to jump back.

17. [DONE] Mobile fixes.
    - Customer vendor page back button is now hidden on phones
      (sm:inline-flex), so it never overlaps the bottom-fixed cart pill
      or the first menu card.
    - Vendor dashboard stats are 2x2 on phones.

18. [DONE] Animations.
    - styles.css: scroll-behavior: smooth on <html> (with reduced-motion
      escape hatch) so anchor-tag clicks (e.g. category cards) glide
      instead of jumping, and scroll-padding-top so anchors don't hide
      under the sticky header.
    - Per-route motion.main fade/slide-in (home, login, cart, quick
      order, orders index, order detail).
    - Vendor cards on home + category cards stagger in with framer-
      motion. Order rows / cart lines / vendor-dashboard orders use
      AnimatePresence for smooth add/remove.
    - Toaster: rich colours, expand, top-center, plus the close button.
      Sonner already provides slide-in/fade-out on toast lifecycle.

# Verification
- npx tsc --noEmit            : clean.
- npm run lint                : 0 errors (only pre-existing shadcn fast-
                                refresh warnings remain).
- npm run build               : both client + SSR bundles built.
- curl smoke test on /, /login, /quick-order, /vendor, /manage, /cart,
  /orders, /vendors/raju  -> all 200, no runtime errors in dev log.
